               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <p>A lead sheet in eight fragments, damaged on top and right sides, apparently preserved on left and perhaps bottom sides. Reported in early publications to be silver, but apparently it is a lead object like all other Sicilian real estate contracts.</p>
                           <material ana="#material.metal.lead" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/115">Lead</material>
                           <objectType ana="#object.lamina" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/145">lamina</objectType>
                           <dimensions>
                              <height unit="cm">5.0</height>
                              <width unit="cm">6.5</width>
                              <depth unit="cm">0.1</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </support>
                        <condition ana="#condition.damaged"/>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>The left side of the text and its margin is completely preserved from L. 4 onward; all other margins are unknown. The text appears to wrap, e.g. from L. 4 to L. 5 where the break is between syllables.</p>
                           <rs ana="#execution.engraved" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/3.html">engraved</rs>
                           <damage ana="#text_condition.incomplete"/>
                           </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>
                        <p>Omicron full size, four-bar sigma, alpha with slanting bar, three-bar upsilon, diagonal strokes of alpha, delta, lambda, sometimes extend past the vertex.</p>
